    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - WATER PUMP AND THERMOSTAT - WATER PUMP - DISASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the water pump impeller as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount the water pump in a vise.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install a suitable puller with the pulling jaws inserted into the 1/2 in. holes of the
                    impeller and the forcing screw on the shaft. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151007">10.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Turn the forcing screw to remove the impeller from the shaft.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the impeller from the housing to expose the water pump seal. Remove the seal from
                    the shaft and discard (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151008">10.8</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Current water pumps are equipped with a one-piece shaft seal. Earlier styles have a
                            separate pump seal and impeller seat.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the hub retaining nut and pulley hub. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151009">10.9</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4151007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg6232" filename="../figcg6/CG6232.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10.7. Remove Water Pump Impeller.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4151008" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12218a" filename="../figcg1/CG12218A.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10.8. Remove Water Pump Seal.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4151009" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10945" filename="../figcg1/CG10945.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10.9. Water Pump Cross-Section .</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front bearing seal and wear sleeve. Discard the bearing seal (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_224.xml" xrefid="ef4151010">10.10</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retaining ring using a ring expander as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_224.xml" xrefid="ef4151011">10.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press out the shaft from the rear of the housing, as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_224.xml" xrefid="ef4151012">10.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The bearings and spacers will come out with the shaft. The bearings must be pressed from the
                        shaft.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive out (from the front of the housing) the metal part of the water pump seal. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151009">10.9</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                for component location. Discard the part.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive out (from the rear of the housing) the rear bearing seal and discard the part. Refer
                to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151009">10.9</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                for component location.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
